  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor @ Jurong Island",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Report to the Project Manager / Deputy Project Manager (Commercial) / Commercial Manager, Commercial Department.</p></li><li><p>Conduct construction market resource research and prepare analysis reports on a bi-weekly basis.</p></li><li><p>Prepare, review and edit tender, bidding and contract documentation.</p></li><li><p>Assist in contract negotiation, clarification and variation works.</p></li><li><p>Manage tendering processes for project subcontracting.</p></li><li><p>Conduct subcontract pricing research, cost analysis and prepare related reports.</p></li><li><p>Liaise and communicate with subcontractors on commercial matters.</p></li><li><p>Prepare commercial and cost-related reports and statistics.</p></li><li><p>Handle progress claims, valuations and settlement with clients and subcontractors.</p></li><li><p>Support project commercial management activities.</p></li><li><p>Perform other duties as assigned by the Company.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements:</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Minimum 3 years of relevant experience as a Quantity Surveyor or in construction commercial management.</p></li><li><p>Degree in Civil Engineering, Quantity Surveying or Engineering Budget Management from a recognised institution.</p></li><li><p>Relevant experience in Singapore construction cost budgeting and commercial practices will be an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Relevant training or certification in contract or commercial management will be an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Must be able to meet site access and security requirements to work in Jurong Island.</p></li><li><p>Able to commence work within short notice will be an advantage.</p></li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
